@speckyspooky . the problem is not the content of the error message as i have mentioned above. The problem is that BIRT returns status 200 when there is an error, it should return status 5XX instead (as http protocol states in case of error).

If you get a 200 status code then it means everything went fine and you can process the response as expected. BIRT responds with status 200 even when there is an error and this is a problem.

@hvdtup It doesn't need to be a REST service, It's not about architecture, it's about http protocol which defines the response status codes.

